<P>
   TERROR-ARREST (Undated) _ When U.S. customs officials arrested
Ahmed Ressam near Seattle last week after he came off a ferry from
Canada in a car they say was loaded with jars of nitroglycerine,
timing devices and other bomb-making materials, American
intelligence officials knew little about him. But the arrest set
off alarms in France, where anti-terrorist officials had been
focusing on the 32-year-old Ressam because of his connections to a
radical Islamic group that French investigators suspect had carried
out in 1996 a series of attacks on supermarkets, armored security
vehicles and banks in northern France. By John F. Burns.
</P>
<P>
   TERROR-BORDER (Buffalo) _ The scene at the border, amid
heightened security. By David W. Chen.
</P>
