and ultimately agreed upon. It's an exercise removed from anything
athletic, a chess match of anticipated moves on a gridiron with
300-pound game pieces. The art of deception is the skill prized
above all others as opponents' tendencies are examined and their
weaknesses weighed. The goal is to play your game with your players
but to look completely different doing it. By Bill Pennington.
