<HEADLINE>
POLA NAMED USC RUNNING BACKS COACH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Former USC fullback Kennedy Pola has been hired as
the Trojans' new running backs coach.
</P>
<P>
   Pola, 36, played fullback and linebacker at USC from 1982-86. He
spent the past season as the linebackers coach at San Diego State.
He was the running backs coach at Colorado from 1997-98, and was at
San Diego State from '94-96.
</P>
<P>
   ``I know SC is a pressure place and I like to be challenged in
my profession,'' Pola said. ``I think I need a challenge. I don't
mind being nervous or held accountable. This is my alma mater and I
have a passion for coaching running backs. It's that simple.''
</P>
<P>
   USC coach Paul Hackett said he will complete his coaching staff
by Friday. The remaining position _ tight ends coach _ could go to
graduate assistant Phil Pettey, who has applied for the job.
</P>
<P>
   Cash expected to sign: Cornerback Chris Cash of Palomar Junior
College (5-foot-11, 180 pounds) is expected to sign his
letter-of-intent today with the Trojans. He is believed to be good
enough to challenge for a starting position next season.
</P>
</TEXT>
