   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   FASHION-MILLER _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ The name ``Nolan
Miller'' isn't as well-known as, say, Calvin Klein or Tommy
Hilfiger. But, guaranteed, Americans are familiar with the Miller
look whether they know it or not. Nolan Miller is the man who
dressed Mary Ann in gingham for ``Gilligan's Island.'' He put Peggy
Lipton in hip huggers for ``The Mod Squad.'' And he created those
linebacker-wide shoulder pads for Krystle Carrington on
``Dynasty.'' (Sturrock, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MARIBEL-ALVAREZ _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Maribel Alvarez
recently bet on a Dolphins game. ``If they won, my friend said
she'd pay for me and another friend to spend a week at Doral
Saturnia,'' she says, referring to the swank Miami spa where
robe-clad socialites agonize over whether to schedule a Swedish
massage or shiatsu. ``If they lost, I'd do some work for her for
free.'' Well, Maribel's going to Miami. And her pal's going to be
out about six grand. Bottom line: Maribel frolics with rich folks.
Really rich folks. (Grantham, Palm Beach) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SHOPPING-GUIDE _ A weekly feature telling how to locate
hard-to-fnd items. This week: Books by Celestine Sibley, clove
stick candy and a vintage Sinatra family Christmas album now
available on CD. (Johnson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH
PHOTOS and LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   NEWS-QUESTIONS _ Q&AMP;A on the news, in two takes. (Bessonnette,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) (EDS: Moving on l (Lifestyle) and a
(General News) categories.) MOVED.
