<P>
   XMAS-BRUNCH _ On Christnas day, the cook responsible for the
holiday dinner is also likely to be the one picking up the wrapping
paper and consulting on the assembly of toys. There's no time, it
seems, to fix brunch. But an easy holiday brunch can be a relaxing
break in a busy Christmas Day. The definition of easy is dishes
that can be mostly made ahead, and that's the key to this brunch
menu. (Dayton Daily News) WITH PHOTOS. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TAMALES _ AUSTIN, Texas _ The Sanchez family has having
tamaladas for at least 25 years. It's always at grandma Sanchez'
home. It's a great time. Four generations and up to 40 family
members (uncles and aunts and cousins) show up every year. They
look forward to it. It's part of their holidays. It's part of their
culture. It's part of their family. (Ricardo, Austin
American-Statesman). WITH PHOTOS. MOVED.
