   &UR; POLITICS (p) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   POLITICS-LOCAL (Portsmouth, N.H.) _ Here in the first primary
state, the issues that voters are most concerned with are not
always lofty matters of national security or domestic policy.
Frequently, they are very local and very personal, having little to
do with the presidency and everything to do with winning or losing
the New Hampshire primary. By Jill Zuckman. 1475 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MILLENNIUM-FEARS (Washington) _ Washington and New York City
have canceled their New Year's Eve balls for lack of interest,
leaving charities in the lurch &UR;  &LR; and entertainers at loose ends. Are
Y2K and terrorism fears keeping America home next week? By Susan
Milligan. 1000 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   JAILHOUSE-HEALING (Boston) _ House of Correction inmates will
find a surprise in their holiday stockings this year. Sheriff
Richard J. Rouse is giving each one a copy of a book that teaches
prisoners to get in touch with their inner child and forgive their
misdeeds. By Judith Gaines. 800 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   DEER-OVERPOPULATION (Boston) _ Fewer deer were killed in
Massachusetts' hunting season this fall than in any of the past
four years _ good news for the animals but bad news for a state
scrambling to rein in the deer population. By Robert Braile. 750
words.
</P>
