   FILM-ANY GIVEN SUNDAY &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ ``Any Given Sunday'' must be the first
almost-three-hour-long movie directed by a man with
attention-deficit disorder: Mr. Stone's Wild Ride. (It looks like
it was edited with a remote control _ a zapper _ since it can
barely remain in place for one shot, let alone an entire scene.)
And there's enough noise and insanity going on to make you think
that the games are played in South Park Stadium. By ELVIS MITCHELL.
Story will move in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-LIBERTY HEIGHTS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Director Barry Levinson continues his onscreen love
affair with 1950s Baltimore, his hometown, in ``Liberty Heights.''
The love affair began with ``Diner,'' still his best picture, and
continued on through ``Tin Men'' and ``Avalon.'' (The Fells Point
Diner from ``Diner'' makes a cameo here.) Levinson, however, has
become more and more imperial as a director. By ELVIS MITCHELL.
Story will move in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FILM-MOTHER &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Writer-director Pedro Almodovar's newest film, ``All
About My Mother,'' is one of the year's best. With it, Almodovar
continues the streak he started with last year's ``Live Flesh,'' a
welcome return to form that wasn't as groundbreaking as his earlier
work, which included ``Women on the Verge of a Nervous Breakdown''
and ``Law of Desire,'' but was arresting nonetheless. By ELVIS
MITCHELL. Story will move in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   F O O D A N D D I N I N G &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   EVOLUTION OF EDIBLES &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ What's past is prologue for our millennium party.
We're celebrating with dishes that can be served at a sit-down meal
or as components on a party buffet. Their other commonality is that
all of these victuals have been around for centuries _ sometimes
much as we know them today, often in a much less evolved state. By
BEVERLY BUNDY. Story will move in ``d'' food and dining category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
