<P>
   CIR-COMPUTER-COLUMN (Undated) _ The weekly computer column: For
many personal computer users, Y2K preparedness has meant getting a
date or finding a baby sitter and having sufficient Champagne and
MP3 party tunes on hand for New Year's Eve. The digital event of
the century is less than 10 days away, and perhaps you are not
quite certain whether you or your PC is going to have the bigger
hangover on Jan. 1. If so, here are some last-minute tips. By Peter
H. Lewis.
