was important enough for a computer language to be named after him,
wrote that God is not merely ''Author of mathematical truths and
the order of the elements...but the God of Abraham,'' Isaac, Jacob.
''The God of Christians is a God of love and consolation.''
 &HT;    Bible-believing scientists founded branches of science:
antiseptic surgery, Joseph Lister; bacteriology, Louis Pasteur;
calculus, Isaac Newton; computer science, Charles Babbage;
comparative anatomy, Georges Cuvier; chemistry, Robert Boyle;
genetics, Gregor Mendel.
 &HT;    Yet in India, millions of Hindus who believe in Jesus refuse to
become active Christians, according to Ralph Winter, founder of the
U.S. Center for World Missions. ''They see Christianity as the
carrier vehicle for alcohol, sexual liberation and tearing down the
family.''
 &HT;    It is up to this generation to reform Christianity to make it
credible to unbelievers.
 &HT;    
 &HT;    ----
 &HT;    c.1999 Mike McManus
