   AIDS-DRUG (San Francisco) _ Three weeks after a company
suspended development of a new AIDS drug because of harsh side
effects, a study at the University of California at San Francisco
indicates that the drug Adefovir is effective for some patients who
have become resistant to other treatments. By ULYSSES TORASSA.
</P>
<P>
   NASA-SHUTTLE (Houston) _ Two astronauts float out of space
shuttle Discovery for the first of three days of spacewalking
repairs to the ailing Hubble Space Telescope. By MARK CARREAU.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SAINTS (New Orleans) _ Even for a franchise that has been as
historically inept as the New Orleans Saints, this season is
shaping up as one of the worst in memory. Between Mike Ditka's
frequent outbursts and Ricky Williams' more-frequent injuries, the
Saints have been a walking and talking disaster area this season.
As they head into their final two games of the season _ and
possibly of the Ditka era in New Orleans _ the Saints see one way
to salvage something from their lost year. And that would be to
knock off the Dallas Cowboys on Christmas Eve. By JOHN McCLAIN.
</P>
<P>
   With: FBN-HERSKOWITZ-COLUMN
