to death and two more beheaded. In Richmond, Va., one was beaten,
stabbed and beheaded. In Seattle, one was stabbed 18 times. They
were all homeless people murdered over the last year. And these
were just the cases that made the news. Exactly how many homeless
people have been victims of savage attacks is unknown, but experts
say the number is rising. By Evelyn Nieves.
</P>
<P>
   NEWYEAR-SITTERS (Undated) _ On New Year's Eve, many of the
1,000-some couples attending the Memphis Junior League's charity
ball at the Peabody Hotel will bring their children along. So the
parents can be free to cavort, they have hired 40 of the Annie's
Nannies agency's adult baby sitters. They will pay the sitters $330
each for the affair and triple the agency's usual rate. So it will
be in most big cities and their affluent suburbs this New Year's
Eve. Teen-age baby sitters stand to earn $200 or $300 for one
night's work and adults up to $400, or more than the tab for many a
partygoer's duck and champagne. By Peter T. Kilborn.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
</P>
<P>
