have developed a technique that might eventually be used to create
monkeys with added human genes, allowing those genes to be
investigated for potential treatments for human diseases. But the
scientists say they are acutely aware that their research, in which
jellyfish genes were installed in monkey embryos, raises a host of
uncomfortable questions about reproductive technology. By Gina
Kolata.
