<P>
   GIFT-CERTIFICATES (Undated) _ Jonas Lee has a Harvard MBA. But
no business school course can possibly prepare you for the daily
frenzy at an Internet start-up like his GiftCertificates.com. The
fortunes of GiftCertificates.com, an online marketer of gift
certificates, will be determined largely by how well it copes with
such mundane matters as order-handling, packing and shipping. And
that means it must deftly manage and motivate the people who do
this work _ not MBAs or techies, the expected dot-com denizens, but
high school graduates. By Steve Lohr.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Display)
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-ONLINE-BIZ (Beijing) _ China's Internet industry has
tantalized outsiders ever since the country's Communist leaders
made it clear that they welcomed the digital revolution. But in the
last six months, the novelty has mutated into a kind of obsession.
With the number of online users tripling in 1999, to nearly 7
million, the Internet in China looks like a here-and-now
opportunity. Foreign technology companies, venture capitalists and
investment banks are all angling for pieces of it. By Mark Landler.
