<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`MARY' HAS GIVEN WAY TO OTHER NAMES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   QUESTION: When did Mary stop being the most popular female name
for babies, and what's the most popular one today? &QL; 
_ L.B.E., Fort Worth, Texas &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ANSWER: The last year that Mary topped the U.S. name popularity
list was 1961, according to Michael Shackleford of the Social
Security Administration. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Mary was the most popular feminine name from 1900 to 1946 and
1953 to 1961. For the past four years, Emily has ranked No. 1. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Shackleford's rankings come from Social Security card
applications for children born during each year. In 1998, the most
popular girl's names after Emily were Hannah, Samantha, Ashley,
Sarah, Alexis, Taylor, Jessica, Madison and Elizabeth. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Boy's names were ranked as follows: Michael, Jacob, Matthew,
Joshua, Christopher, Nicholas, Brandon, Tyler, Andrew and Austin. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I find a poster of Rebecca Lobo of the New York
Liberty? My 11-year-old daughter is a big fan. &QL; 
_ M.V., Northboro, Mass. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A: No posters turned up for Lobo, but the official WNBA store
sells an 8-by-10 photo of her with Lisa Leslie for $5 and a black
replica Lobo jersey for $42. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   For ordering information or a free catalog, call (800) 711-3879
or visit the Web site store.nba.com/wnba.html. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I contact the model Amber Valletta? &QL; 
_ M.R., Cleburne, Texas &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Valletta in care of Elite Model, 111 E. 22nd St.,
New York, NY 10010. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The 25-year-old model has been cast in several films next year,
including the Harrison Ford thriller ``What Lies Beneath'' and
``Family Man'' with Nicolas Cage.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
