<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FRONTPAGE-NYT </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   (pr) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Here are the stories New York Times editors are planning for
Page 1, Thursday, Dec. 23. The N.Y. Times News Service Night
Supervisor is Pat Ryan; phone: (888) 346-9867; e-mail:
patryan(at)nytimes.com.
</P>
<P>
   TOP
</P>
<P>
   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   NJ-POLICE-PROFILING (Trenton, N.J.) _ Citing extensive evidence
that New Jersey State Police officers have discriminated against
minority motorists, the Justice Department announces that it will
appoint an outside monitor to oversee the police agency and to
insure that it enacts reforms to deter racial profiling. By David
Kocieniewski. (We plan to move the story by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   Top center: 3-column photo reefer to SCI-SHUTTLE; story inside.
</P>
<P>
   Off-lead story:
</P>
<P>
